  "text": "PBK's actions through p38 and ERK signaling were also shown in glioblastoma stem-like cells [CITATION_1] . Levels of phospho-p38 MAP kinase (Thr180/Tyr182) were down-regulated in GBM CSC cultures treated with HI-TOPK-031 and those featuring shRNA mediated knockdown of PBK [CITATION_2] . Down-regulation of PBK also induced significant reduction in phosphorylated ERK1/2 levels [CITATION_3] thus confirming the results obtained in other cancers [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
